 subject.  It was there so I could get a feel for what, exactly, everyone was interested in.  My impressions (and these should be the same as everyone else's, if you read all the opinions and &quot;votes&quot;) is that there are two definitive schools of thought on POG...one is &quot;reserve it like the old planes,&quot; the other is &quot;First come, first served,&quot; or &quot;whoever gets their first wins.&quot;<br>
<br>
So the real vote will end up between these two ideas.  However, we can't vote without some semblance of orderly rules for either of the two ideas.  Thus, in the next few days, I'll be carefully reading the comments in the &quot;POG -- Discussion and Ideas please&quot; thread that I started in this forum, and attempting to hammer out something vaugely resembling a consensus from all the ideas in there.  Actually, two consensuses (or is that &quot;consenses&quot;)...one for FCFS, the other for reservations.<br>
<br>
So, to cut through the crap, if you have an idea as to HOW we should go about doing either reservations or FCFS in POG, regardless of which school of thought you belong to, go post it on that thread.  The more resources I have, the better off we all are. <p><BR>
